## Docker standalone builds for production

Next.js standalone output reduces Docker images from ~547MB to **~110-200MB** by tracing only required dependencies. Enable it and use a 4-stage Dockerfile:

```dockerfile
FROM node:22-alpine AS base

FROM base AS deps
COPY package.json package-lock.json* ./
RUN npm ci

FROM base AS builder
COPY --from=deps /app/node_modules ./node_modules
COPY . .
RUN npm run build

FROM base AS runner
ENV NODE_ENV=production
RUN adduser --system --uid 1001 nextjs
COPY --from=builder /app/public ./public
COPY --from=builder --chown=nextjs:nextjs /app/.next/standalone ./
COPY --from=builder --chown=nextjs:nextjs /app/.next/static ./.next/static
USER nextjs
CMD ["node", "server.js"]
```

**`NEXT_PUBLIC_*` variables are inlined at build time** and cannot change at runtime. Pass them as Docker build args. Server-only environment variables (database URLs, secrets) work at runtime.

